OperatorInfo.Title: Ecotricity
OperatorInfo.Comments: Pay-as-you-go, app-based charging, mostly at Motorway Services in the UK

UserComments.Comment: Right hand unit Chademo wouldn't start charge due to failure to lock. Two vehicle queue for only CCS unit.
busy place
Both units in use, and two other queueing vehicles.

CheckinStatusType.Title: Charging Spot In Use (Other EV Parked)

UserComments.Comment: Right hand unit. Chademo. Slow charge, only 7.4kWh in 22 minutes, average 20kW. Free vend. Outside air temperature 2℃
Left hand unit (Chademo/CCS) out of action, offline and with DC errors, Right hand unit went onto free vend just as I plugged in. Charged fine with Chademo.
Chademo charged fine on left-hand unit. Offline, hence Free vend.
Chademo charged okay, an e-Golf had just CCS charged okay
CCS OK
Exceedingly busy. Had to queue for over 40 minutes.  Two cars queueing behind me

CheckinStatusType.Title: Charging Spot In Use (Other EV Parked)

UserComments.Comment: Both charging units were working perfectly at lunchtime today.
Very busy indeed. Two leafs charging, two waiting, and a Tesla on charge next door.
All working.  They still haven't painted the correct bay markings in front of the AC/CHAdeMO unit
Working perfectly on the 1st of August and on return journey on the 2nd.  As previously noted it was very busy and another leaf had to queue to use the Fast Charger.
Very busy site. Two vehicles queueing for a CHAdeMO charge.
Site now has two DBT chargers: CCS / CHAdeMo and AC / CHAdeMO, next to Tesla's two Superchargers.

Ecotricity are replacing their chargers, it looks like there's likely to be the standard set of Chademo / CCS / AC rapids, the old AC type 2 post has been removed, and there's foundations for new chargers being installed at the moment.

CheckinStatusType.Title: Failed to Charge (Equipment Not Fully Installed)

UserComments.Comment: Tesla's adjacent charging station now up and running. Haven't seen any customers there, but a queue for the chademo.
Had to wait 10 minutes, but all good
First Rapid charge, just so I get used to the process. Found the point still thinking it was charging. Worked out the rather convoluted emergency stop and reset buttons and the am charging a bit.

A very popular location. The last few visits, I've had to queue for the CHAdeMO. Luckily, there's a 22kW post next to it, so you can get some charge while waiting. Shame my leaf can only make use of 6.6kW of that.
Good times! Pity there's no fast AC in but there seem to be cables for more charge stations in the ground.
Working great!
Charged Peugeot Ion (i-Miev) sucessfully on the Chademo but had to wait 30 mins for a Leaf to finish.
22kw charger northbound working great
Had to wait 10 min for another leaf to finish. First time I've had to wait anywhere!
Charger let me set 100% 23/10/2013
New fast charger is fantastic
Have charged my Leaf at 16A several times with no problems.

MediaItems.Comment: Nearly a full house. New Ecotricity chargers in place and operational. The old AC 22kW charger has gone.
